<subSubSection lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1436,1520,2013]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1772,1797]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
Name proposed to distinguish 
<taxonomicName authority="Brocchi, 1814 sensu Auctores" authorityName="Brocchi, 1814 sensu Auctores" authorityYear="1814" box="[624,1249,1772,1797]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Scalaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pseudoscalaris">
<emphasis box="[624,896,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Scalaria pseudoscalaris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[905,1065,1772,1797]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref81158" refString="Brocchi, G. B. (1814) Conchiologia fossile subapennina con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. 2 Vols. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 56 + 80 [Roman numerals] + 712 pp., 16 pls." type="book">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
sensu Auctores
</taxonomicName>
, considered as a distinct species by Monterosato based on the lack of spines at the axials. The alleged synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1814" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1814" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Scalaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lamellosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Scalaria lamellosa</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1814
</taxonomicName>
(from Western Atlantic) was initially considered as possible by Monterosato’s (1877d: 420) but subsequently (Monterosato, 1878c: 26) rejected. Some Authors have considered the introduction by Monterosato as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1822" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1822" box="[597,983,1916,1941]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Scalaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lamellosa">
<emphasis box="[597,808,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Scalaria lamellosa</emphasis>
Lamarck, 1822
</taxonomicName>
[not 
<taxonomicName authority="Brocchi, 1814" authorityName="Brocchi" authorityYear="1814" box="[1041,1407,1916,1941]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lamellosum">
<emphasis box="[1041,1243,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Turbo lamellosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1250,1407,1916,1941]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref81158" refString="Brocchi, G. B. (1814) Conchiologia fossile subapennina con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. 2 Vols. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 56 + 80 [Roman numerals] + 712 pp., 16 pls." type="book">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
— now 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brocchi, 1814)" authorityName="Brocchi" authorityYear="1814" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[207,676,1952,1977]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Cirsostrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caenogastropoda, ordo incertae sedis" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lamellosum">
<emphasis box="[207,482,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cirsostrema lamellosum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[499,666,1952,1977]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref81158" refString="Brocchi, G. B. (1814) Conchiologia fossile subapennina con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. 2 Vols. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 56 + 80 [Roman numerals] + 712 pp., 16 pls." type="book">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
]. 
<bibRefCitation box="[695,922,1952,1977]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" refId="ref85849" refString="Landau, M., La Perna, R. &amp; Marquet, R. (2006) The Early Pliocene Gastropoda (Mollusca) of Estepona, Southern Spain. Part 6: Triphoroidea, Epitonioidea, Eulimoidea. Palaeontos, 10, 1 - 96, 22 pls. [Palaeo Publishing and Library vzw]" type="book chapter">
Landau 
<emphasis box="[787,845,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
(2006
</bibRefCitation>
: 18) debated the issue of the name to use for the species, deciding for 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monterosato)" authorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[440,881,1988,2012]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Epitonium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="commutatum">
<emphasis box="[440,710,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Epitonium commutatum</emphasis>
(Monterosato)
</taxonomicName>
[now 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Monts Ann. Museo Civ. Genova" authorityYear="1876" box="[957,1206,1988,2013]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Gyroscala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="commutata">
<emphasis box="[957,1206,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Gyroscala commutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]. Considering other cases of species from the two sides of the Atlantic almost indistinguishable morphologically (see e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bruguiere, 1792" authorityName="Bruguiere" authorityYear="1792" class="Gastropoda" family="Bullidae" genus="Bulla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[1295,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Bulla striata</emphasis>
Bruguière, 
<date box="[278,334,188,212]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" value="1792-05">1792</date>
</taxonomicName>
v. 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Adams, 1850" authorityName="A. Adams" authorityYear="1850" box="[371,738,188,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Bullidae" genus="Bulla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[371,538,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">B. occidentalis</emphasis>
A. Adams, 1850
</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation box="[750,1032,188,213]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref86241" refString="Malaquias, M. A. E. &amp; Reid, D. G. (2008) Systematic revision of the living species of Bullidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Cephalaspidea), with a molecular phylogenetic analysis. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 153, 453 - 543. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2008.00369. x" type="journal article">Malaquias &amp; Reid, 2008</bibRefCitation>
) we take a conservative position in regarding the introduction by Monterosato (1877d: 420) as a new species. In case the two entities (Eastern v. Western Atlantic) are considered as conspecific, then the name for both should be 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monterosato, 1877)" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1877" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Gyroscala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="commutata">
<emphasis box="[1180,1436,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Gyroscala commutata</emphasis>
(Monterosato, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
; in case they are proved (for instance by genetics) as distinct, then 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1160,1314,296,320]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Gyroscala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="commutata">
<emphasis box="[1160,1314,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">G. commutata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be restricted to the Eastern Atlantic species. Recorded by MolluscaBase (2018) as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lamarck, 1822)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1822" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Gyroscala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lamellosa">
<emphasis box="[1204,1436,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Gyroscala lamellosa</emphasis>
(Lamarck, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
, we suggest reverting to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monterosato, 1877)" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[628,1116,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Epitoniidae" genus="Gyroscala" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neotaenioglossa" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="commutata">
<emphasis box="[628,877,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Gyroscala commutata</emphasis>
(Monterosato, 1877)
</taxonomicName>
as taxon inquirendum [
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">new status</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
